column3: Automatic sanity-testing: PASSED, see http://jenkins.bluematt.me/pull-tester/595b6d88d41c0cadf9411b3aaef5585e2060e739 for binaries and test log.\nThis test script verifies pulls every time they are updated. It, however, dies sometimes and fails to test properly.  If you are waiting on a test, please check timestamps to verify that the test.log is moving at http://jenkins.bluematt.me/pull-tester/cu
That's one of those magic numbers that we should perhaps constantify?\n

It may be that using the explicit numbers here actually makes the rules more readable than using a named constant. OTOH some form of documentation as to why certain numbers were chosen in the source code would be useful.\n
